## Communication Paths

### **Development Environment**

```
Developer Machine ←→ Development Server
  Protocol: HTTP/HTTPS
  Port: 8000 (default Django)
  Purpose: Local development and testing
```

---

### **Production Environment**

#### **Path 1: Client to Web Server**
```
Client Device ←→ Load Balancer ←→ Web Server
  Protocol: HTTP/HTTPS
  Port: 80 (HTTP) / 443 (HTTPS)
  Purpose: User requests and responses
```

#### **Path 2: Web Server to Database**
```
Web Server ←→ Database Server
  Protocol: TCP/IP (PostgreSQL/MySQL) or File I/O (SQLite)
  Port: 5432 (PostgreSQL) / 3306 (MySQL)
  Purpose: Database queries and transactions
```

#### **Path 3: Web Server to File Storage**
```
Web Server ←→ File Storage Node
  Protocol: File System I/O (local) or REST API (cloud)
  Purpose: File upload, read, delete operations
```

#### **Path 4: Load Balancer to Multiple Web Servers**
```
Load Balancer ←→ Web Server 1
Load Balancer ←→ Web Server 2
Load Balancer ←→ Web Server N
  Protocol: HTTP/HTTPS
  Port: 8000-8010 (internal)
  Purpose: Load distribution
```

---

### **Cloud Environment**

#### **Path 5: Client to Cloud**
```
Client Device ←→ Internet ←→ Load Balancer ←→ Cloud Application Server
  Protocol: HTTPS
  Port: 443
  Purpose: Secure web access
```

#### **Path 6: Application to Cloud Database**
```
Cloud Application Server ←→ Cloud Database Service
  Protocol: TCP/IP (encrypted)
  Port: Managed service port
  Purpose: Database operations
```

#### **Path 7: Application to Cloud Storage**
```
Cloud Application Server ←→ Cloud Storage Service
  Protocol: REST API (HTTPS)
  Port: 443
  Purpose: File storage operations
```

